        <description>Android Studio is a new Android development environment based on IntelliJ IDEA. Similar to Eclipse with the ADT Plugin, Android Studio provides integrated Android developer tools for development and debugging. 

**On top of the capabilities you expect from IntelliJ, Android Studio offers:**


* Gradle-based build support.
* Android-specific refactoring and quick fixes.
* Lint tools to catch performance, usability, version compatibility and other problems.
* ProGuard and app-signing capabilities.
* Template-based wizards to create common Android designs and components.
* A rich layout editor that allows you to drag-and-drop UI components, preview layouts on multiple screen configurations, and much more.

**Optional Command Line Parameters**

* To pin Android Studio to the taskbar pass in: /PinnedToTaskbar:true

* To create a desktop icon for Android Studio pass in: /AddToDesktop:true


	
		cinst AndroidStudio -packageParameters "/PinnedToTaskbar:true /AddToDesktop:true"</description>
